They cannot sugarcoat their romantic feelings by labeling the relationship as friendship. They can be aggressive too. But they are honest, full of adventure and with an enthusiasm for life. Both Venus and Mars represent passion and sensuality and amalgamation of their energies leads to excessive sexual feelings and attraction. Venus in Aries also gives a tendency to show interest in others’ spouses. They are also irreligious and quite driven towards the materialistic or indeed corporeal aspects of life. They do nonetheless possess an attractive personality. They are artistic beings, with strong inclination towards creative pursuits, beauty and fine arts.

current_sade_sati.description: Sadhe Sati refers to the seven-and-a-half year period in which Saturn moves through three signs, the moon sign, one before the moon and the one after it. Sadhe Sati starts when Saturn (Shani) enters the 12th sign from the birth Moon sign and ends when Saturn leaves 2nd sign from the birth Moon sign. Since Saturn approximately takes around two and half years to transit a sign which is called Shanis dhaiya it takes around seven and half year to transit three signs and that is why it is known as Sadhe Sati. Generally Sade-Sati comes thrice in a horoscope in the life time - first in childhood, second in youth & third in old-age. First Sade-Sati has effect on education & parents. Second Sade-Sati has effect on profession, finance & family. The last one affects health more than anything else.

personal_characteristics.personalised_prediction: Since the  1st lord, Sun is in the 10th house, Authority and leadership shape your career. Following in your father’s footsteps or carving a path in government or politics suits your commanding presence.

Since the  2nd lord, Mercury is in the 10th house, Your authority will stem from working in large organizations where communication is key. You may become a successful businessman or corporate worker, using analytical skills in the finance sector.

Since the  3rd lord, Venus is in the 9th house, You will love to travel to far distant places and will love to meet new people of different cultures. You will also be inclined towards higher studies and different philosophies. You will have an interest in the occult. Your partner may even be of a different culture.

Since the  4th lord, Mars is in the 9th house, You shall have lots of arguments with your teachers and with people in authority. You will have to struggle with your mother and in your home. You will be a strong and headstrong person but will have  to put efforts for higher learning.

Since the  5th lord, Jupiter is in the 12th house, You shall become an extremely spiritual person. You can be an astrologer, a mystic, or anything you want in this field. Your children may even go to foreign lands. You will have high spiritual growth. You can also possibly work as a foreign diplomat.

Since the  6th lord, Saturn is in the 1st house, You will be burdened with disputes in the early part of life. You will get success only when you put in the best efforts. You are likely  to suffer from a sense of underachievement in life.

Since the  7th lord, Saturn is in the 1st house, Everything that you desire will be delayed till your mid-thirties. You shall have to marry late to have a good married life. You shall have a stable relationship. More than romantic needs your relationship will be based on practical needs.

Since the  8th lord, Jupiter is in the 12th house, You can be a successful motivational speaker, guide, or guru. You will be knowledgeable and very good speakers. you may have a career in counseling or education. You can also work as financial planners. Your father too may be a rich person. You shall also gain from the government.

Since the  9th lord, Mars is in the 9th house, Your a headstrong person and faithful to your religious beliefs. You will assess individuality in the field of higher education or religion. You can even get into physical fights.

Since the  10th lord, Venus is in the 9th house, You shall be naturally inclined towards traveling and meeting people of different cultures. You shall visit far-off lands for work and will get involved in a relationship with some person at work. You shall assert great individuality.

Since the  11th lord, Mercury is in the 10th house, You will have a career in the field of wealth and finance. You may be working in the banking institutions in the position of a manager. You shall be working in the stock market  dealing with shares and shareholders.

Since the  12th lord, Moon is in the 1st house, You shall be a self-centered person and can be mean at times. You will work in the hospitals as you like taking care of people and that will shape your personality and life path. You will be a creative person.

response.name: Red Coral
response.description: Coral is a calcareous, skeleton-like deposit of the coral polyp- a tiny invertebrate that dwells in quiet waters and is found at depths ranging from 20 to 1,000 feet. The color of coral depends on the depth at which it is found. The color usually ranges from white to pink to vermilion red and deep scarlet. A good coral that is related to the planet Mars and recommended by astrologers, gem therapists and jewelers is a deep red coral, which resembles well- ripened bimb fruit or an unripe cherry. If the gemstone has flaws it will affect your life negatively

flaw_results.flaw_effects: Suffering in career and well being

response.time_to_wear_short: One hour after sunrise till 11 AM
response.time_to_wear: A coral should be bought on a Tuesday when the Moon is in Aries or Scorpio, when any of the four nakshatras Mrigshira, Chitra, Annuradha, or Dhanishtha is present. The coral should be bought between sunrise and 11.00 A.M. The stone should be set so that it touches the skin. The coral's weight should be no less than 6 carats. The metal used should be a mixture of copper and gold - any other metal should not be used in the mixture. Preparing a ring on a Tuesday when the Moon is in Capricorn is very auspicious. Best time to wear is one hour after sunrise till 11 AM
response.methods: Before wearing the ring for the first time, immerse it in raw cow's milk and wash it in Ganga water, rainwater, spring water, or water kept in a copper pot for some time. After being washed, the ring should be placed on a red cloth on which a numerical Mars Yantra is drawn with red sandalwood paste, gorochan (a red calcium from cowhorn), saffron, or roli. The yantra and the gemstone set in the ring should be worshiped by reciting the mantra of Mars.

planet_report_ketu.planet_definitions: Ketu, the mystical planet, guides the journey of spirituality, detachment, and liberation. It offers insights from past life experiences, urging a release from material attachments. Ketu's enigmatic influence encourages seeking deeper truths and transcending worldly bonds.
planet_report_ketu.gayatri_mantra: Om Chitravarnaya Vidmahe Sarparoopaya Dheemahi Tanno Ketuh Prachodayaat
planet_report_ketu.qualities_long: This placement prompts him to detach from conventional relationship expectations and embrace spiritual connections, leading to many opportunities for personal growth and expansion through his ability to form authentic and spiritually meaningful partnerships.
planet_report_ketu.qualities_short: A spiritually attuned and detached partner.
planet_report_ketu.affliction: An afflicted Ketu may lead to challenges in conflicts or issues related to detachment or difficulties in forming balanced and fulfilling partnerships.
planet_report_ketu.personalised_prediction: 8th house is the house of transformations, mystery, magic, wealth, accidents, gains, health, setbacks and so on. And when Ketu occupies this house, the native is strongly inclines towards metaphysical realms. It is positive for the mystical side of your life. There is a strong chance that the native may adopt occultism as a profession. Such a person has a very strong intuition and psychic abilities. They are natural healers.
planet_report_ketu.planet_zodiac_prediction: The ruling planet of Aquarius is also Saturn and both are friendly to each other. Saturn is the significator of detachment from the materialism and Ketu is also associated with spiritual liberation. People born with Ketu in Aquarius are quite learned and understand the reality of life. But despite this knowledge, they struggle to get rid of their desires. Ketu in Aquarius gives never-ending desires to the person. Saturn also relates to social service and so does Aquarius. Ketu’s placement further aggravates one’s inclination towards benevolent tasks. Ketu is an airy planet and when it is positioned in Aquarius, the native tends to make unrealistic plans and has unnecessary desires. This position of Ketu also makes the native prone to ear related problems. These people get success in life but belatedly. They are quite strict and stubborn in nature. It is quite difficult to convince them to make a change against their wish. These people also inherit health issues from their family. Their relationship with friends and their own children does not flourish much. Instability in income is also possible for these natives. Ketu in Aquarius also boosts one’s chances to travel abroad.
